    "Lora training of the attention mechanism is shown in Fig. 3.",
    "As a quick summary, let us assume that we have original weight matrix W 0 2 R d k.",
    "LoRA works by adding a low-rank matrix to the original weight matrix: ΔW + W 0, ΔW = BA where B 2 R d r and A 2 R r k.",
    "Note that one should choose r (minðd; kÞ and only adapt the attention weights to ensure constraints on the dimensionality of the new weights and preserve original model performance.",
    "Training is only performed on this ΔW, and original model weights are kept the same."
  ],
